ntract for $30-million investment in Quebec interconnect upgrade</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/20\">Government of New Brunswick - Latest News</a>) NB Power has awarded a contract to the Swedish firm ABB to begin investing $30 million in an upgrade to the Eel River high-voltage direct current converter station, located near Dalhousie.</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 27, 2013 7:18 a.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www2.gnb.ca:80/content/gnb/en/news/news_release.2013.02.0156.html\"><span class=\"post_title\">Provincial government champions Pink Shirt Day</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/20\">Government of New Brunswick - Latest News</a>) The provincial government is reaffirming its stand against bullying within schools, communities and workplaces by encouraging New Brunswickers to observe the sixth annual national Pink Shirt Day, today, Wednesday, Feb. 27.</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 7:15 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.newbrunswickbeacon.ca/29738/trudeau-tackles-ei-reform-energy-plans-nb/\"><span class=\"post_title\">Trudeau tackles EI reform and energy plans in NB</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/author/27\">Makedonia Koutsoumpeli</a></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/21\">The New Brunswick Beacon</a>) The Liberal Party will undo the recent employment insurance changes, if and when elected to power, said Justin Trudeau during his campaign in Fredericton earlier today. The front-runner in the leadership race for the Liberal Party said the Conservative governments EI reforms are a terrible piece of legislation, that affects New Brunswickers, all the Atlantic [...]</span></p>\r\n<div><s