ars would be redeveloped, therefore forcing the shop out. Luckily though, the long-loved comic store will be able to stay downtown; Strange Adventures will move into a bright space with big windows in the lovely Georgian building on the corner of Prince and Lower Water streets (5110 Prince Street, the former home o...</span></p>\r\n<div><span style=\"float:right;\"><p><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/entertainment.htm\">Entertainment: The Province</a></p></span></div>\r\n</section>\r\n\r\n<section id=\"sports\">\r\n<div class=\"section\"><p>\r\n<h2>Sports</h2>\r\n<p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 9:51 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.atlanticuniversitysport.com/sports/mice/2012-13/releases/20130226z79yjp\"><span class=\"post_title\">Top-ranked V-Reds skate past Panthers 5-1 to advance to AUS final</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/50\">AUS Headlines</a>) (CHARLOTTETOWN, P.E.I.) - The CIS No. 1-ranked UNB Varsity Reds defeated the UPEI Panthers 5-1 in Subway AUS men&#x2019;s hockey semifinal action Tuesday night to claim their best three-of-five series 3-1 and advance to the AUS championship final series against the Saint Mary&#x2019;s Huskies.</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 9:28 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.moncton-wildcats.com/article/wildcats-explode-on-the-eagles\"><span class=\"post_title\">Wildcats explode on the Eagles</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/author/-1\"></a></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/4\">News</a>) </span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 3:26 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.atlanticuniversitysport.com/aotw/20130226_Week21\"><span class=\"post_title\">Subway AUS Athletes of the Week: Dalhousie\'s McCulloch and UNB\'s Myatt honoured</s