s=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/4\">News</a>) Grand prize won by three BMO Ultimate Fans - one each from the Western Hockey League (WHL), the Ontario Hockey League (OHL) and the Quebec Major Junior Hockey League (QMJHL), as part of BMO Ultimate Fan Appreciation Night Series</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 25, 2013 8:10 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.pointstreaksites.com/view/miraclesbasketball/news/news_67406\"><span class=\"post_title\">Miracles Win Fourth Straight Against The Rainmen</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/author/211\">News Articles</a></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/45\">NBL: Moncton Miracles News Articles</a>) </span></p>\r\n\r\nReports<br><br>\r\n\r\n   </div>\r\n   <div class=\"span5\">\r\nNews Media<br><br>\r\n<p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 9:51 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.atlanticuniversitysport.com/sports/mice/2012-13/releases/20130226z79yjp\"><span class=\"post_title\">Top-ranked V-Reds skate past Panthers 5-1 to advance to AUS final</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/50\">AUS Headlines</a>) (CHARLOTTETOWN, P.E.I.) - The CIS No. 1-ranked UNB Varsity Reds defeated the UPEI Panthers 5-1 in Subway AUS men&#x2019;s hockey semifinal action Tuesday night to claim their best three-of-five series 3-1 and advance to the AUS championship final series against the Saint Mary&#x2019;s Huskies.</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 3:26 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.atlanticuniversitysport.com/aotw/20130226_Week21\"><span class=\"post_title\">Subway AUS Athletes of the Week: Dalhousie\'s McCulloch and UNB\'s Myatt honoured</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/50\">AUS Headlines</a>) (HALIFAX, N.S.) - Rob McCulloch of the Dalhousie Tigers men\'s track and field team team and Sarah Myatt of the UNB Varsity Reds women\'s track &amp; field team are the Subway AUS Athletes of the Week for the period ending February 24, 2013.</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 24, 2013 10:54 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.atlanticuniversitysport.com/sports/mice/2012-13/releases/2013022495v9z3\"><span class=\"post_title\">Peters stars again as Huskies shutout Axemen 1-0 to advance to Subway AUS championship series</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/50\">AUS Headlines</a>) (WOLFVILLE, N.S.) &#x2013; The CIS No. 5-ranked Saint Mary&#x2019;s Huskies shutout the Acadia Axemen 1-0 in Wolfville Sunday night to win their best three-of-five Subway AUS men&#x2019;s hockey semifinal series 3-1 and advance to the AUS championship final series.</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 24, 2013 8:46 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.atlanticuniversitysport.com/sports/wice/2012-13/releases/20130224quo9va\"><span class=\"post_title\">No. 5-ranked X-Women claim 9th AUS banner with 4-1 victory over Huskies</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/50\">AUS Headlines</a>) (SACKVILLE, N.B. ) - The CIS No. 5-ranked StFX X-Women capped off an impressive season with a 4-1 victory over the Saint Mary\'s Huskies in the championship final at the 2013 Subway AUS women&#x2019;s hockey championship hosted by Mount Allison University.</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 24, 2013 7:15 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.newbrunswickbeacon.ca/29688/frederictons-skating-season-shrinks/\"><span class=\"post_title\">Fredericton&#8217;s skating season shrinks</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/author/235\">Bridget Yard</a></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/21\">The New Brunswick Beacon</a>) Fredericton may have marketed itself as a winter wonderland for its Frostival campaign last month, but its winter landscape is changing. The weather in Fredericton  like many other Canadian cities- is getting warmer each year, and some recreational activities are suffering. Kyla Tanner grew up practicing her hockey skills on an outdoor rink. She [...]</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 24, 2013 8:51 a.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.atlanticuniversitysport.com/sports/fball/2012-13/releases/20130224cf12c5\"><span class=\"post_title\">StFX`s Don Loney to be inducted into Canadian Football Hall of Fame</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/50\">AUS Headlines</a>) OTTAWA (CIS) &#x2013; Brian Fryer, a standout running back and receiver at the University of Alberta, and the late Don Loney, a legendary coach at St. Francis Xavier University, are about to become immortalized in Canadian football history.</span></p>\r\n   </div>\r\n\r\n   <div class=\"span4\">\r\n\r\nColumn<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\nBlogs<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n   </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div><!-- FOOTER: Site footer for links, copyright, etc. -->\r\n<div id=\"footer\" style=\"margin-top:50px;\">\r\n<a rel=\"license\" href=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/\"><img alt=\"Creative Commons License\" style=\"border-width:0\" src=\"http://i.creativecommons.org/l/by-nc-sa/3.0/88x31.png\" /></a> \r\n<a  href=\"http://grsshopper.downes.ca/about.htm\"><img alt=\"gRSShopper\" style=\"border-width:0\" src=\"http://course.downes.ca/assets/img/gRsshopper_88x31.png\"></a><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCopyright 2013 Moncton Free Press ~ \r\n