downes.ca/city.htm\">City</a></li>\r\n      <li class=\"\"><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/province.htm\">Province</a></li>\r\n      <li class=\"\"><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/canada.htm\">Canada</a></li>\r\n      <li class=\"\"><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/world.htm\">World</a></li>\r\n      <li class=\"\"><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/economy.htm\">Economy</a></li>\r\n      <li class=\"\"><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/entertainment.htm\">Entertainment</a></li>\r\n      <li class=\"\"><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/sports.htm\">Sports</a></li>\r\n      <li class=\"\"><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/opinion.htm\">Opinion</a></li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n</header>\r\n\r\n     \r\n     <!--GENERATED CONTENT BEGINS  --><h1>Canada</h1>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row-fluid\">\r\n  <div class=\"span12\">\r\n     <div class=\"span3\">\r\nPress Releases<br><br>\r\n<p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 6:18 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://cupe.ca/child-care/stroller-derby-planned-christy-clarks\"><span class=\"post_title\">&lsquo;Stroller Derby&rsquo; planned for Christy Clark&rsquo;s office</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/7\">News | Canadian Union of Public Employees</a>) Event marking International Women&#8217;s Day to call on premier to bring in child care plan</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 3:06 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://cupe.ca/disability-rights/strong-presence-blindnesslow-vision\"><span class=\"post_title\">Strong presence for CUPE at blindness/low vision forum</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/7\">News | Canadian Union of Public Employees</a>) NEW WESTMINSTER&#8212;CUPE made its presence known at a unique weekend forum aimed at raising awareness about and improving the lives of people with blindness and low vision.</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 2:02 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://cupe.ca/quebec/fire-chief-offers-regrets-montreal\"><span class=\"post_title\">Fire Chief offers his regrets - Montreal municipal workers react bitterly</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/7\">News | Canadian Union of Public Employees</a>) &#8220;Too little, too late&#8221; was the reaction of the Syndicat des fonctionnaires municipaux de Montr&#233;al (CUPE 429) to the mea culpa from the director of the Service de s&#233;curit&#233; incendie de Montr&#233;al. Serge Tremblay took to the media Sunday to acknowledge ongoing problems with psychological harassment within the Montreal fire department.</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 12:58 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://cupe.ca/cupe-national-convention/alberta-hold-50th-anniversary\"><span class=\"post_title\">CUPE Alberta to hold 50th Anniversary Convention in Fort McMurray</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/7\">News | Canadian Union of Public Employees</a>) EDMONTON &#8211; The Alberta Division of the Canadian Union of Public Employees will hold its 50th Anniversary Convention in Fort McMurray March 20-22 at the Sawridge Hotel.</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 12:58 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://cupe.ca/british-columbia/wear-pink-february-27\"><span class=\"post_title\">Wear Pink on February 27</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/7\">News | Canadian Union of Public Employees</a>) CUPE members across BC are encouraged to wear pink tomorrow, February 27, in support of National Anti-Bullying Day. By wearing pink, CUPE members will take a stand against bullying and bring awareness to this serious problem in schools, workplaces, and communities.</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 10:50 a.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://cupe.ca/pensions/send-message-hands-pension-plan\"><span class=\"post_title\">Send a message: Hands off our pension plan</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/7\">News | Canadian Union of Public Employees</a>) Click here to send an email to the Local Authorities Pension Plan telling them to leave our retirement benefits alone!</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 25, 2013 5:46 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://cupe.ca/pensions/lapp-update-february-25th-2012-crisis\"><span class=\"post_title\">Pension plan update &ndash; why there is no crisis</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/7\">News | Canadian Union of Public Employees</a>) CUPE has been sounding the alarm about proposed changes to the plan that would reduce retirement benefits available to members of the Local Authorities Pension Plan (LAPP).</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 25, 2013 3:38 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://cupe.ca/economics/cupes-battle-wages-proves-fraser\"><span class=\"post_title\">CUPE&#8217;s &#8220;Battle of the Wages&#8221; proves Fraser Institute wrong</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/7\">News | Canadian Union of Public Employees</a>) The Fraser Institute is rolling out a series of reports attacking public sector workers, which glosses over the statistical evidence, and ignores previous research that counters their ideology.</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 25, 2013 1:30 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://cupe.ca/bargaining/supportive-housing-peel-get-serious\"><span class=\"post_title\">Supportive Housing in Peel needs to &lsquo;Get Serious&rsquo; and bargain fair agreement, says CUPE 966 President</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/7\">News | Canadian Union of Public Employees</a>) Supportive housing services in the Region of Peel are unnecessarily being placed at risk, the President of Local 966 of the Canadian Union of Public Employees (CUPE 966) warned today.</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 24, 2013 10:39 a.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://cupe.ca/women/report-prompts-action-parliament\"><span class=\"post_title\">Report prompts action in parliament for missing and murdered Aboriginal women</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/7\">News | Canadian Union of Public Employees</a>) A motion put forward in the House of Commons by Liberal MP Carolyn Bennett called for the formation of a special committee to conduct hearings on nearly 600 documented cases of missing or murdered Aboriginal women in Canada. The committee would have one year to report its findings and recommendations to parliament.</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 24, 2013 8:59 a.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://pm.gc.ca/eng/media.asp?id=5327\"><span class=\"post_title\">PM to welcome French Prime Minister Jean-Marc Ayrault to Canada</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/author/283\">CDATA(10)</a></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/35\">Stephen Harper / Prime Minister</a>) Prime Minister Stephen Harper today announced that he will welcome Jean-Marc Ayrault, Prime Minister of the French Republic, to Ottawa on March 13-14, 2013, as part of his official visit to Canada.\r\n&ldquo;Canada&rsquo;s relationship with France is rooted in our deep historic, cultural and linguistic ties. Our countries are key commercial partners and cooperate closely on global issues of strategic importance,&rdquo; said the Prime Minister. &ldquo;I look forward to welcoming Prime Minister Ayra...</span></p>\r\n\r\nReports<br><br>\r\n\r\n   </div>\r\n   <div class=\"span5\">\r\nNews Media<br><br>\r\n\r\n   </div>\r\n\r\n   <div class=\"span4\">\r\n\r\nColumn<br><br>\r\n<p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 10:00 a.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.threehundredeight.com/2013/02/ontario-polls-point-to-volatile.html\"><span class=\"post_title\">Ontario polls point to volatile electorate</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/author/2\">ric</a></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/6\">ThreeHundredEight.com</a>) </span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 25, 2013 2:48 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.threehundredeight.com/2013/02/bc-ndp-gains-outside-of-vancouver.html\"><span class=\"post_title\">B.C. NDP gains outside of Vancouver</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/author/2\">ric</a></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/6\">ThreeHundredEight.com</a>) </span></p>\r\n\r\nBlogs<br><br>\r\n<p><span class=\"post_date\">February 27, 2013 3:28 a.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://sixthestate.net/?p=8002\"><span class=\"post_title\">Reason No. 217 Why an Ambassador for Religious Freedom is a Silly Idea</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/author/3\">Sixth Estate</a></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/14\">The Sixth Estate</a>) I just about fell off my chair when the Globe &#38; Mai