>\r\n</section>\r\n\r\n<section id=\"canada\">\r\n<h2>Canada</h2>\r\n<p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 6:18 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://cupe.ca/child-care/stroller-derby-planned-christy-clarks\"><span class=\"post_title\">&lsquo;Stroller Derby&rsquo; planned for Christy Clark&rsquo;s office</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/7\">News | Canadian Union of Public Employees</a>) Event marking International Women&#8217;s Day to call on premier to bring in child care plan</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 3:06 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://cupe.ca/disability-rights/strong-presence-blindnesslow-vision\"><span class=\"post_title\">Strong presence for CUPE at blindness/low vision forum</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/7\">News | Canadian Union of Public Employees</a>) NEW WESTMINSTER&#8212;CUPE made its presence known at a unique weekend forum aimed at raising awareness about and improving the lives of people with blindness and low vision.</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 2:02 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://cupe.ca/quebec/fire-chief-offers-regrets-montreal\"><span class=\"post_title\">Fire Chief offers his regrets - Montreal municipal workers react bitterly</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/7\">News | Canadian Union of Public Employees</a>) &#8220;Too little, too late&#8221; was the reaction of the Syndicat des fonctionnaires municipaux de Montr&#233;al (CUPE 429) to the mea culpa from the director of the Service de s&#233;curit&#233; incendie de Montr&#233;al. Serge Tremblay took to the media Sunday to acknowledge ongoing problems with psychological harassment within the Montreal fire department.</span></p>\r\n<br><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/canada.htm\">Read More: Canada</a><br>\r\n</section>\r\n\r\n<section id=\"world\">\r\n<h2>World</h2>\r\n<p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 7:31 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.dailymaverick.co.za/article/2013-02-27-seth-macfarlane-says-no-way-he-would-host-oscars-again/\"><span class=\"post_title\">Seth MacFarlane Says \'No Way\' He Would Host Oscars Again</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/67\">Daily Maverick</a>) Comedian Seth MacFarlane said on Tuesday that he would not host the star-studded Academy Awards ceremony again, after TV critics panned Sunday\'s show.</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 7:31 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.dailymaverick.co.za/article/2013-02-27-obama-highlights-the-defense-hit-in-budget-cuts-battle/\"><span class=\"post_title\">Obama Highlights The Defense Hit In Budget Cuts Battle</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/67\">Daily Maverick</a>) President Barack Obama took his case for softening the effect of deep budget cuts to a shipyard town dependent on defense contracting on Tuesday, but there was little sign he will be able to halt automatic cuts from starting this week. By Mark Felsenthal.</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 7:31 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.dailymaverick.co.za/article/2013-02-27-big-powers-offer-iran-some-sanctions-relief-await-reply/\"><span class=\"post_title\">Big Powers Offer Iran Some Sanctions Relief, Await Reply</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/67\">Daily Maverick</a>) Major powers offered Iran limited sanctions relief in return for a halt to the most controversial part of its atomic work during the first day of nuclear talks on Tuesday, and Iran promised to respond with a proposal on the same scale. By Yeganeh Torbati and Justyna Pawlak.</span></p>\r\n<br><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/world.htm\">Read More: World</a><br>\r\n</section>\r\n\r\n<section id=\"economy\">\r\n<h2>Business and Economy</h2>\r\n<p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 9:22 a.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.michaelgeist.ca/content/view/6793/135/\"><span class=\"post_title\">Internet Surveillance Bill is Dead but Canada\'s Telecom Transparency Gap is Alive and Well</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/author/231\">Michael Geist</a></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/54\">Michael Geist Blog</a>) The government\'s recent decision to kill its online surveillance legislation marked a remarkable policy shift. The outcry over the plan to require Internet providers to install surveillance capabilities within their networks and to disclose subscriber information on demand without court oversight sparked an enormous backlash, leading to the tacit acknowledgment that the proposal was at odds with public opinion. While many Canadians welcomed the end of Bill C-30, my weekly technology law column (...</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 7:46 a.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.statcan.gc.ca/daily-quotidien/130226/dq130226a-eng.htm\"><span class=\"post_title\">Payroll employment, earnings and hours, December 2012</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/37\">Statistics Canada, The Daily</a>) Average weekly earnings of non-farm payroll employees were $908 in December, up 0.3% from the previous month. On a year-over-year basis earnings increased 2.8%.</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 7:46 a.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.statcan.gc.ca/daily-quotidien/130226/dq130226b-eng.htm\"><span class=\"post_title\">Quarterly financial statistics for enterprises, fourth quarter 2012</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/37\">Statistics Canada, The Daily</a>) Canadian corporations reported $72.5 billion in operating profits in the fourth quarter, up 1.4% from the previous quarter.</span></p>\r\n<br><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/economy.htm\">Read More: Business and Economy</a><br>\r\n</section>\r\n\r\n<section id=\"entertainment\">\r\n<h2>Entertainment</h2>\r\n<p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 2:25 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.thecoast.ca/RestaurantandBarNews/archives/2013/02/26/fid-bids-farewell\"><span class=\"post_title\">Fid bids farewell</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/author/187\">Allison Saunders</a></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/27\">Halifax, Nova Scotia | THE COAST, The Coast Halifax</a>)         When Fid Resto (1569 Dresden Row, 422-9162) announced that it&#x2019;d be closing in late May, people freaked out a little. Saddened by the loss, the internet threw around dismayed comments about the decline of downtown Halifax and landlord accusations, while in reality it turns out that Dennis Johnston and Monica Bauche just want to take a much-deserved breather, and the end of their lease was good timing.&#x2026;            \n[ Read more ]        \n[ Subscribe to the comments on this sto...</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 1:21 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.thecoast.ca/Shoptalk/archives/2013/02/26/strange-adventures-new-home\"><span class=\"post_title\">Strange Adventures\' new home</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/author/621\">Alyssa Gallant</a></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/27\">Halifax, Nova Scotia | THE COAST, The Coast Halifax</a>)         Late in 2012, Calum Johnston got the news in that &#x201C;eight to 12 months&#x201D; the building that his Strange Adventures (5262 Sackville Street) called home for over 20 years would be redeveloped, therefore forcing the shop out. Luckily though, the long-loved comic store will be able to stay downtown; Strange Adventures will move into a bright space with big windows in the lovely Georgian building on the corner of Prince and Lower Water streets (5110 Prince Street, the former home o...</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 5:51 a.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://musicnerd.ca/believe-in-celtic-woman/\"><span class=\"post_title\">Believe In Celtic Woman</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/author/215\">Ken Kelley</a></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/44\">The MusicNerd Chronicles | The MusicNerd Chronicles</a>) The talents of vocalists Chlo Agnew, Lisa Lambe and Susan McFadden, and violinist Mirad Nesbitt, collectively known as Celtic Woman, have been dazzling audiences worldwide since the group&#8217;s formation in 2004. They have become a[...]</span></p>\r\n<br><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/entertainment.htm\">Read More: Entertainment: The Province</a><br>\r\n</section>\r\n\r\n<section id=\"sports\">\r\n<h2>Sports</h2>\r\n<p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 9:51 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.atlanticuniversitysport.com/sports/mice/2012-13/releases/20130226z79yjp\"><span class=\"post_title\">Top-ranked V-Reds skate past Panthers 5-1 to advance to AUS final</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/50\">AUS Headlines</a>) (CHARLOTTETOWN, P.E.I.) - The CIS No. 1-ranked UNB Varsity Reds defeated the UPEI Panthers 5-1 in Subway AUS men&#x2019;s hockey semifinal action Tuesday night to claim their best three-of-five series 3-1 and advance to the AUS championship final series against the Saint Mary&#x2019;s Huskies.</span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 9:28 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.moncton-wildcats.com/article/wildcats-explode-on-the-eagles\"><span class=\"post_title\">Wildcats explode on the Eagles</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/author/-1\"></a></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/4\">News</a>) </span></p><p><span class=\"post_date\">February 26, 2013 3:26 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.atlanticuniversitysport.com/aotw/20130226_Week21\"><span class=\"post_title\">Subway AUS Athletes of the Week: Dalhousie\'s McCulloch and UNB\'s Myatt honoured</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/50\">AUS Headlines</a>) (HALIFAX, N.S.) - Rob McCulloch of the Dalhousie Tigers men\'s track and field team team and Sarah Myatt of the UNB Varsity Reds women\'s track &amp; field team are the Subway AUS Athletes of the Week for the period ending February 24, 2013.</span></p>\r\n<br><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/Read More: Sports</a><br>\r\n</section>\r\n\r\n<section id=\"opinion\">\r\n<h2>Opinion</h2>\r\n<p><span class=\"post_date\">February 20, 2013 3:26 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.sackvilletribunepost.com/Opinion/2013-02-20/article-3181273/THE-GREEN-BACKPACK-%26ndash%3B-Mass-media-moving-away-from-Climate-change-coverage/1\"><span class=\"post_title\">THE GREEN BACKPACK  Mass media moving away from Climate change coverage</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></sp